 FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utanilaelanys.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tanilae Lanys</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://web.infoave.net/~tajulian/svanimicon.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Tank Girl</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>3/5/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>9:29:18 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://web.infoave.net/~tajulian/tanilae.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Loss</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">A wolf howls.<br>
<br>
Tanilae looks up from her meditations and cocks her head to one side. 'There are no wolves on the lands of the Iksar ..' she thinks, and looks around.  Miles stretched out before her, and not a lupine creature could be found.  Yet still, the howl came to her ears.<br>
<br>
Closing her eyes, the young elven Ranger returned to her meditation, and heard the words ... a howl carried across the oceans on the winds ... a howl from the lips of a fellow Ranger.<br>
<br>
&quot;Our Beloved Klind has been called to serve Brell .. he has left us, on this land, to watch over us from another plane of Life.&quot; it said, and then was gone.<br>
<br>
Silence.<br>
<br>
And then, slowly, Tanilae opens her eyes to look around her.  The emerald green shimmers with her tears, not yet given leave to fall.  She has one battle yet before she may allow herself to react.  The giant comes ... and in a flurry of motion, her sword and claws flashing against the giant's form .. Tanilae strikes against it alone.<br>
<br>
A scream.<br>
<br>
Of victory, for though beaten and bloody, Tanilae has come out victorious at last.  Now ... after stripping the creature of its few posessions, she turns and walks back to the city, and to the boat which will carry her home.<br>
<br>
Home to the Butcherblock mountains ... where even now she has not brought herself to attack the dwarven people, though an old hatred for them burns in her heart.  Because of her love for a few, she will not destroy the many. One of those is the same Dwarven Cleric the howl brought news to her of.<br>
<br>
Tears.<br>
<br>
As her feet hit the earth, tears begin to fall, unbidden and yet unfettered down her cheeks.  She mours this day, for the loss of a man she was proud to call friend, brother .. even uncle, though she never would tell him to his face. Tears, leaving trails down her dust-caked skin, mark her trail as she walks, unable to bring to mind the words of the magicks granted her by Tunare's love that would speed her path.<br>
<br>
Passing the gates of the Dwarven hold, Tanilae drops to her knees. Her packs fall beside her, yet she does not seem to take notice.  In the night, the fires outside light her face with an eerie light as she weeps for her fallen friend, unmindful of the passers by who look upon her strangely.<br>
<br>
Darkness.<br>
<br>
Settled all around her like a blanket.  Tanilae takes comfort with the cover of night, making her way back to her own home .. Kelethin.  There she can find comfort .. in a few pints of ale, a home cooked meal .. and in that place, East of the city, where she goes to be alone.<br>
<br>
Some will seek her out and ask what it is she does all alone in the middle of the Faydark.  Her answer to them is this: &quot;A great man has been taken from us .. from my family.  I do not understand the reasons.  I will wait here ... until I know why.&quot;<br>
<br>
And so .. still she waits ... unwilling to move, or be moved, until she comes to a conclusion, finds the answers her heart needs to continue.<br>
<br>
